	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=13385><span id=Scholar>Neptunis</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>278 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.15]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Well I agree with most of what you said, but I don't think Sentient is the way to go for a Gnome.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Gnomes strength is his INT, there is no need for the extra INT from the Sentient.  He is weak in STR and STA, so Crustatian Shell Armor would be a better fit.  Also some higher AC items than both of these sets offer would be nice and for that I'd fill in with Darkforge, probably the BP and at least 1 bracer.<br><br>To start I'd recommend some faster weapons, but the MoSS is a keeper.  If you get a Ornate Runed Blade (19/30 2hs +3 sv all) and either a Centi Short Sword (12/24 +5 STR/STA) or Crystalline Short Blade (10/24) you'll be hitting for the full damage cap on all weapons but hitting faster so doing more damage till mid-20's.  I'd also strongly recommend you get a good shield, best bet being the Clay Guardian Shield (25AC +50 HPs) but cheaper versions like the Velium Round Shield will do you well till the 30's.  If you don't see a MoSS cheap get a Smoldering Brand as a good training 1hb weapon, it's fast, hits good and procs from lvl 1.<br><br>Try to eventually get a Hero Bracer for the extra STR, a Bracer of Scavenging is a nice AC +DEX bracer which usually goes cheap and Gauntlets of the Black are outstanding for AC and STR untill you get planes stuff.<br><br>Neptunis Rex<br>lvl 55 DE Revenant<br><br>p.s.  If you thought the DE was weak, you won't like the Gnome, they are very similar in stats and power.  You might want to try the Large Race SK, and then twink with Sentient.  Either way, good luck</p>&nbsp;<br>Neptunis Rex<br>lvl 62 DE Gravelord<br>Have Axe, will travel</td></td></tr>
